Which operating systems support the creation of derived objects? (Select all that apply.)
A. Windows XP
B. Red Hat Linux
C. HP-UX
D. Windows ME
Answer: A,B,C
What versions can participate in a deliver operation?
A. Checked in versions
B. Active versions
C. Inactive versions
D. Checked out versions
Answer: A
What cleartool command do you use to list the derived objects created by clearmake or
omake?
A. catcs
B. ls -la
C. lsdo
D. diffcr
E. catcr -flat
Answer: C

Which of the following statements describe development streams? (Select all that apply.)
A. Are defined by a set of baselines and activities
B. Provide the ability to work in a parallel development environment
C. Determine which versions of elements appear in a view
D. Provide the ability to share completed work
E. Isolate an individual's work from others
Answer: A,B,E
What must be mounted in order for you to work in your UCM snapshot view?
A. Your NFS client
B. Your PVOB only
C. All public VOBs
D. Your host's file system (access to your local hard drive)
Answer: D
How can you obtain a summary of element changes and version information for a given
activity?
A. Use the History Browser.
B. Compare the elements with their predecessors.
C. Compare the elements with their change set predecessors.
D. View the change set for the activity.
Answer: D

A. Your PVOB only
B. Your component VOBs only
C. Your private VOBs
